Sentencas: The Sc-doped La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8-xScxO3-delta(LSCFScx, x=0, 0.04, 0.08) cathode powders were synthesized by a sol-gel method.
Titulo: Crystal Structure and Electrochemical Performance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8-xScxO3-δ Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The crystal structure, chemical morphology of surface elements, catalytic activity and electrochemical properties of LSCFSc cathode material were systematically analyzed.
Titulo: Crystal Structure and Electrochemical Performance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8-xScxO3-δ Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: XRD results show that LSCF has a cubic structure, and the LSCFSc cathode material changes from cubic to hexagonal structure.
Titulo: Crystal Structure and Electrochemical Performance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8-xScxO3-δ Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: The conductivity of LSCFSc cathode material decreases with the Sc3+ doping, and the conductivity of LSCFSc0.08 cathode sample is still greater than 100 S/cm in the temperature range of 300-800 degrees C. XPS results show that Sc3+ doping increases the content of adsorbed oxygen (O-Ads) on the surface of LSCFSc cathode material, and the R-ASR of polarization surface of LSCFSc0.08 cathode material measured at 800 degrees C is 0.026 ohm center dot cm(2), which is about 87.7% lower than R-ASR of LSCF cathode material, which significantly improves the adsorption/dissociation ability of LSCFSc cathode material to oxygen, and enhances the catalytic activity of oxygen.
Titulo: Crystal Structure and Electrochemical Performance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8-xScxO3-δ Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell

Sentencas: Ni-SDC as the anode material, SDC as electrolyte, and LSCFSc0.08 as cathode material assembled into Ni-SDC|SDC|LSCFSc0.08 anode-support single cell, the maximum power density is 806 mW/cm(2) at 800 degrees C, indicating that Sc3+ doping can significantly improves the electrochemical performance of cathode materials.
Titulo: Crystal Structure and Electrochemical Performance of La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8-xScxO3-δ Cathode Materials for Solid Oxide Fuel Cell
